I love prof Carnegie. She is one of my favorite profs at uOttawa. She always answers emails and is available for office hours. Very inconsiderate of her students! Did midterm review A MONTH after the midterm and when asked to view the midterm for feedback, she declined. Places ALL blame on students.

The lectures from the profs are clear and not difficult to understand but the content is extremely heavy. The lectures are jam packed but most of her questions were taken straight from the slides. She's not the easiest but also not the hardest. Since it was online, she did asynchronous lectures which I don't like in general. She definitely knows what she's talking about. Assignments easy af as well.

Dr. Carnegie is definitely one of the better anatomy professors. Her lectures go into a lot of detail and while they do take long to get through, she is very clear in explaining the concepts. Only downside is her midterms/exams are very challenging with each question involving understanding on multiple topics.

Dr. Carnegie is a strong anatomy prof. Her lectures are very well-detailed. Although her tests are tough, she provides sufficient resources for you to pass with flying colours!

Exams were very hard, a good understanding will not get you through, you need to know minute details and you will not be given be given a lot of time to figure it out nor will you be able to go back to questions you are unsure of.  She does do a great job at explaining concepts in her lectures and you can boost your grade with smaller assignments

Definitely the best anatomy prof at the school. Her lectures are super concise and zoom office hours are very helpful- she shows multiple choice questions similar to exams and explains them, plus answers any questions people have. Also recommend for 1106 and 1107.

I really love Carnegie. She takes her time in the lectures, so it is not stressful to listen. She is attentive to detail, and very clear about what we need to know for exams, but also within the field. I look forward to her lectures.

For a class being taught by 8 profs, she has 3 questions on the final exam and they are extremely clear. She won't post questions that came from somewhere that is not seen! Everything you need to know is based on slides. Had her for ANP1107, PHS3341 and PHS4336. Planning to take more ANP/PHS with her!

Dr Carnegie is a solid choice for this course! Her midterms and final weren't bad if you studied and were well prepared. Pretty content heavy course. Dr. Carnegie does not deserve the bad reviews, she puts in so much effort for her students to feel prepared in the medical field. As long as you keep up, she provides every piece of information you need for her tests

Prof Carnegie is probably the best ANP professor compared to the others. Her exams are kinda difficult but if you studied efficiently you should get a decent mark. Her first midterm is the hardest so dont get discouraged. 2nd midterm and final exam are definitely easier. Focus on her lecture slides and read the textbook!

Exams were TOUGH. You had to know the ins and outs of everything you learned, the mcq were the hardest part bc they're so specific. It was asynchronous with video lectures she posted. She is lowkey overhyped on here bc she seemed average to me and was kinda passive-aggressive during office hrs towards students who didn't do as well as others

Honestly worst teacher ever, her lectures are so long that you literally just lose focus and dont learn anything in my class - we had to do a part of our grade was mastering A&P quizzes which I liked about the way she set that up but besides that her lectures were very boring all over the place and hard to comprehend and want to learn more.

Dr. Carnegie's class was really interesting. She explained concepts well and is accessible via email (responds quickly) and office hours (attend them!!). You will have to know the concepts well though so make sure you understand (crash course on Youtube was really helpful).

She's really tough. Its pretty hard to get a decent mark especially after she changed her way of teaching and grading since this year. Don't expect to do decent without maximum effect in this class. switch profs if you can, this rating is NOT accurate and many people agree.

She is an amazing teacher and seems like the sweetest lady ever! She provides so many extra clinical examples and office hour questionsto help you learn the content and how to think like a health care worker. Her exams are fair and truly test if you know the content. I highly recommend her!

Dr. Carnegie is a competent professor and a solid choice for anatomy and physiology. She is familiar with how students learn and will provide a number of ways to self-test and enhance learning. Her exams are fair, and her office hour sessions are helpful. 10/10 would recommend!

Carnegie is a great lecturer and very thorough! Everything you need to know can be found on her slides! She seems like a very nice person, and like she wants you to succeed but her exams are wayyyy harder than the other anatomy profs from what I can tell. Super specific questions that even google doesn't know the answer to.

Not a bad professor, but definitely makes you work for your mark. Exams are reasonable to get an 80+ if you start studying a week ahead. Because people were cheating and using the internet last year she has made her midterm 10x harder honestly trusted the people in here that said she was good but I wish I didn't and just taken another prof. cuz their midterm and exams were wayyy easier than Carnagie. Professor Carnegie was honestly a great professor. She was very engaging but did talk a little slow (use 1.5x speed for recorded lectures). Really good prof. Easy to get an A+ if you try. You don't have to read the book if you go to class.

Overall a good professor! There are lots of opportunities to boost your grades with assignments and crosswords. The lectures are also pretty decent. A solid choice for a professor!

Such a great anatomy prof! I learnt so much and enjoyed her lecture immensely. Her exams are fair but still challenging so make sure to take good notes and understand the lectures. If you have the opportunity to take one of her classes, don't hesitate!

Dr. Carnegie is a very good prof, she explains stuff very well, and watching her lectures was never boring. She tells you exactly what you need to know for the midterms. She is really good, organized lectures, fair exams and a fair grader. She talks a little slow but since this was an online class, you can make the videos speed up more. All in all, I recommend her, I purposefully choose her for my courses. She also likes dogs so how could you resist.

Lots of content, but what do you expect from anatomy. Make sure to attend her lectures, & not just rely on the book. never went to a class. got an A+

rComments: This class is not an easy one! Carnegie's sections (Blood and GI) are easily the best part because she is such a great lecturer. 2 other profs teach as well, but they pale in comparison to her. Get ready to work hard to understand some concepts!

I decided to take this course because she was teaching it. she is one of the best prof, very clear on what to expect and her exam questions are always straight to the point. she had 2 other profs in this course who were really bad their questions were all kind of games. the course is pretty heavy with 60% final :x (Don't take unless you have to)

Comparing to other instructors at this "university", she is god. Physiology is really the best class in the biomedical sciences program, the rest in terrible. The only thing, her guest lecturer, Hebert, for the kidney section, he was terrible, but the rest was interesting and inspiring.

Really good teacher, her class is lecture heavy. Study the textbook and her slides because she likes to give alot of extra details in her lectures that isn't necessary. Her hw is a great grade booster. Not approachable, but i would for sure take her again

Carnegie is good but is not approachable. She gives the rare smile here and there. She knows alot and shes honest saying 1106 aint no breeze. But its doable and you will learn alot from it. Get ready to get fat while studying for her exams because you get hungry for some reason. After all this talking, i want pizza. HAVE FUN!

Dr. Carnegie is a great prof and does a superb job at preparing her students for her exams. She really does emphasize what you should know for exams so I wouldn't miss a lecture. Didn't crack open the textbook once. Keep up with reviewing slides and you'll be fine. She does speak quickly but coming from a slow typer, she was not bad at all!

Super nice teacher, will help you understand confusing concepts. Slides are available outside of class and are easily understandable. Didn't use the textbook throughout the class as the online assignments and crosswords are enough help. Super interesting class!
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Carnegie's a solid choice. She's clear, concise, and gives lots of examples. Attendance is important, she leaves gaps and questions in her slides and often mentions  details and examples not included in her slides.  However her slides are for the most part complete and cover the important topics. Bring coffee to her class. You'll need it.

She speaks very fast, but overall not bad. I did not like slides with missing information, because it is hard to follow during lecture. Major issue, she did not bring back our exams and she gave only one hour window for everyone to go see exam results at the hospital. Not approachable.

I did all the ANP classes with Dr. Carnegie, back in 2011-2012 and she was amazing. I took PHS3341 and she ended up teaching the endocrinology portion of it. She is an amazing lecturer. She explains thing in a way that is easily understandable. Her portion of the final exam was very fair. She wants you to apply the knowledge, rather than memorize.

Dr. Carnegie is an amazing professor! She may move fast in lectures but there is A LOT of material and she does reiterate important info. She is extremely clear about her expectations, especially on her exams and takes the time to give students a breakdown of the exam. Online HW is good mark booster and useful for studying.

She is an incredible prof who knows her stuff. She is clear and lays things out well. There is a lot of content in these ANP courses, but she makes it clear. Lectures are fast, but they have to be to get through it all.

What's the point of a prof when you have to teach the content to yourself?? She speaks waaaay too fast, & if you look around a lecture on any given day, you'll see that she has put almost every other person to sleep. I gave up going to the lectures after the 1st midterm & did MUCH better studying on my own for the 2nd one & the final!

The content is very vocabulary heavy. Carnegie speaks very fast, going back and forth between her slides. Her slides are also an overall mess. If you just study from the textbook, and review your notes on a regular basis, using her ppts as a guideline, you will be fine. The anatomy of the human body never changes so buy a used textbook!
Hard class, a lot of new information, study your ass off, FAST speaker
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things', 'Respected']

rComments: Clear in her expectations for students. Attending class is not mandatory if you study the textbook, but I would still recommend going to them. She is very intelligent, answers questions accurately, and gives clear explanations. The online HW is an easy grade booster. Overall, very solid prof who makes anatomy FUN.

Had Savory for ANP1105 first semester and was a huge mistake. Dr. Carnegie is literally a beauty, and her midterms are completely fair. She taught 2/3 of the course and I've never had such a clear prof when it came to midterms. Memorize the slides and find past midterms and you will be fine. Best ANP prof there is!

I have enjoyed all classes taken with Dr. Carnegie. She is the only prof that I've had that I've felt she actually cares about your education which is rare in University. She knows her stuff and can answer questions effectively. She talks a lot during her lectures but if you listen it's not all heavy content. Definitely get her for any anatomy!

ANP is SUCH a struggle for me, but Carnegie is freaking awesome. She is super well-organised. ANP is damn tough as there's a crapload of material to learn (that can't be helped; the human body is so complex!), but Carnegie is always very fair with exams. Excellent prof; TAKE ANP WITH CARNEGIE EVERY TIME! I had her for 1105, 06 & 07, thank goodness!

ONLY TAKE ANP WITH CARNEGIE!!!  she's one of the best profs I've had and gives you the tools you need to do really well in anatomy. I had different profs first semester for ANP1105 and the difference in my grades is incredible. Don't take anatomy with anyone else if you can help it!!

Great prof, everything for the midterms was very organized and her teaching is effective and captivating. She goes incredibly fast because there is a lot of material. Exams are average for difficulty overall, but the diagram section is very difficult. Use the textbook a lot, and try to study every diagram you find.
Lectures were great, tests are fairly straight forward. She's one of the better ANP profs, so definitely try to have her as your prof if you take this class
Her exams are pretty tough compared to other anatomy profs, but she is a sweet lady with good lectures.

I have taken ANP1105, ANP1106 and ANP1107 with Carnegie.  It IS a hard class, but ALL Anatomy classes are and as far as profs I've had teach it, she is the best and I do everything I can do get in her class because she is clear in her expectations of students and doesnt put unfair questions on her exams. The class is hard but she makes it possible.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Loved Carnegie for 1105, loved her again for 1107! So sweet, knows her stuff, makes her expectations super super clear. Love her :)

She is a great prof, very clear on what will be graded and teaches very well- organized, precise, gives good/relevant info... Her midterms are blessed, it is all off her slides and info that you can actually remember. If you're taking anatomy and don't want to suffer for a whole semester, pick Carnegie!

Carnegie is by far the best anatomy prof. her slides are clear as is she. she is very helpful and quite easy to follow. you still have to read the textbook but you don't feel completely abandoned by her!!
Taking ANP1105 with her was fun, her lectures are super clear.

Carnegie is a good prof. Stick with her for the ANP courses and don't cram the material just before the exams and you will do well. Her exams are MCQ's with some labelling questions. No tricky questions. Know the material and you will do well
Totally loved her lectures! Amazing prof! Just do the readings and mastering and pay attention in class

This course is quite difficult as their is TONS of material to be learned. However, Carnegie is quite a good prof. She totally knows what she's talking about. I had to work my butt off to pass this course, but it's not the prof's fault, I respect her.
3rd time having Carnegie - this prof is gold. Lots of material, but you can't avoid that. Really fair exam questions! She doesn't trick you. Understand/memorize the material and you're solid.

Lectures were slightly dry, but all the information you need is on the powerpoints (only used the textbook for diagram labelling practice), and she knows her stuff. Midterms and final was VERY fair, and if you know the info on the powerpoints you will do really well. Mastering A&P was an awesome grade booster, and a great way to prepare for exams.
Excellent prof: clear, consistent expectations, organized.  As long as you keep on top of the material you'll do fine. Don't ever get behind though! A lot of information and details in this class.
She is an amazing lecturer and a very nice person. Love her way of presenting the material, and expectations are extremely clear! Makes anatomy fun and charming

Definitely get Prof. Carnegie for anatomy if you can! She is amazing! She makes everything super clear, even though the course material is challenging. I didn't really use my textbook, but I probably should have. Overall a great class! Make sure you leave lots of study time for the exams and do the Mastering assignments (an easy 7%).
She's very nice, but very boring. The class is hard because there's sooo much material to learn, but in terms of a professor, I would recommend her.

Good prof. However, course material is VERY tough.  ANP1105 will help you SO much in this class. Most of the material she covers is not in the bio textbook so you basically have to listen to her speak and try to copy as much stuff down as possible. Just listening to her in her lectures is not sufficient to pass with an A!! Use your resources!

She explains everything really well and has lots of videos and other resources to reinforce concepts. She is a very sweet lady. Her midterm was fair. A lot of content so youmust read and organize yourself but the material can be very interesting.
Great Lecturer, everything you need to know is on her slides. She tells you what you need to know for the exam. Do her practice questions!

DO MASTERING ANP (easiest 10%, answers on quizlet). Boring lectures, slides full of words (could've been made easier to study from). Txtbk only need to compliment what you don't understand (read all readings for 1105, then only studied slides for 6 + 7 and got same mark). Exam questions fair, look at previous exams on notebro, often same Qs

Do not take the anatomy series of courses with another professor. Very clear in her expectations on midterms during the lecture, so make sure to pay attention. Can be tricky with her diagrams, so make sure you study ALL (and I mean ALL) of the applicable ones!
LOVE LOVE LOOOVVVVEEE HER! Very clear, study and memorize what she gives you and the midterms and exam are a breeze!
Great prof!

Excellent professor. There is a lot of material but her slides really focus in on what to know. Paying attention in lectures also really helped me on tests as a lot of the material she emphasizes in class is also emphasized on tests.
Don't take Anatomy with anyone else!!! She is very clear on what she wants from you, attending the lecture and paying attention to what she says is the key!

Best anatomy professor I've had - I had her for ANP1105 as well, and part of ANP1107. She's very clear about her midtermsfinals, but the questions are tricky. You can usually find her old midterms online though, and she barely changes them.
The class is a very straight forward memorization course. Study from the textbook using her slides as reference.

She's very clear about the material and her expectations. There is a lot of information but she tries to make it memorable and make sense. Mastering A&P is an absolute lifesaver, the modules and "Flix" videos let you really visualize what's going on. The textbook is also fantastic quality and should be used as sometimes the powerpts are more vague.

Carnegie talks crazy fast! Once you learn to keep up with her pace you will ace the course. Don't read the textbook, listen to her. The textbook has way more info then you need to know. If you pay attention in class she tells you exactly what you need to know for tests. Find old midterm of notebudd, because she reuses some of her old question.

Although there is a lot of information in these course, Carnegie is very clear in what she expects you to know! Midterms and final were very fair. Everything you need to know is in her slides and shat she expands on in class. However, she does speak quickly! Download her ppts and add notes. Mastering is a good grade booster. Super cute prof!

Carnegie is a great professor. But you really need to take the time and put in the effort or you will not succeed. Despite the fact that the material can be dry and monotonous at times, she tries her best to keep the class' attention. Definitely recommend for the ANP classes. PPT's coincide with textbook. Exams are fair if you study.

She is such a sweet lady and really cares about the people in her class. The class itself is difficult and a lot of time must be put in to get decent grades. Lots of help is available, I highly recommend going to study groups.  SHE IS AN ANGEL THOUGH, CHOOSE HER OVER ANY OTHER PROF

Awesome prof! She is very clear and makes getting a good grade very possible if you are willing to put in the work. A lot of reading and memorization is required but you will learn a lot by the end of the course! Get her as a prof if possible!
Don't forget to do the online assignments that everyone forgets about.
Really good prof, very knowledgeable and good at explaining the material. There is a lot of content, but she has clear expectations for exams.

Dr. Carnegie is honestly an amazing prof. Anatomy is very interesting but there is lots of detail and she makes it very understandable. Exams are easy but you must put effort into understanding not just memorizing material. Also get to know her, Dr. Carnegie is always super helpful and takes time out of her day to answer questions.

She is understanding. i couldn't submit my assignment on time becausei didn't have the textbook,the bookstore ran out of the textbook. unlike other professors, she offered me more time to get the textbook and she was going to open the assignment online. she gives in class quizzes without grading just to improve your knowledge while she teaches

Carnegie is an awesome lecturer. That being said, prepare to be taught A LOT of information. She is very specific in how you write the short answer questions, but she will tell you how you should write them. She is one of the better profs in this course. Take it if you liked ANPs. If you didn't, this is not the course for you.

Had Carnegie for ANP1105. Took ANP1106 with her. She's an awesome prof. Her notes give you all the info to do well. Anatomy classes aren't easy so you have to put time and effort into them. Lectures can be dry. Read the textbook and take notes. Midterms were fair. Once you get used to her, you'll for sure do well. Assignments are a booster!!

She is one of many profs that teach this class but in my opinion, one of the worst. Her slides have too much information and she doesn't take a break when she talks. She is very particular on HOW you answer her questions. Exams are moderate-hard, uses a lot of diagrams in her exams. This class is A LOT of work, don't take it if not necessary.
Similar to ANP1105. Still a very chill professor, and is very clear in what she expects from you. Attend her lectures and you'll be golden.
Super nice professor and easy to follow, even though she seems somewhat bland in the beginning. You'll love this class if it's with her.
Really good teacher. She explains everything amazingly and organizes her lectures to match the textbook.

Nice and helpful but will put you to sleep. Her midterms and exam were all multiple choice (with basic labelling/fill in the blanks) - easier compared to other profs. Her ppwts may be confusing at times. You will do well if you memorize her ppwts but you should refer to the textbook in the areas where her words lack clarity. Easy A+ if you do this.

Simply, one of the best professors in uOttawa (if not THE best). She is crystal clear on her expectations, gives very manageable exams, and actually cares about her students' success. ANP courses are difficult, but she makes them interesting and useful. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND her for any course she's involved in.
Jackie Canegie's Teaching Skills  > Every Other Prof. Honestly, she's amazing. I learned so much from her. I highly recommend her course.

AWESOME! Read the powerpoints, listen to her in class, get A+. Repeat for ANP1106 and ANP1107. She is super fair in her expectations, and even though she was a pretty easy examiner, I still learned more in her classes than any other class I took this year. She's one of few science profs with a Masters in Education - that really says something

What can I say; love me some JAC. No prof in the entire institution can hold a candle to her. She teaches what she expects you to know, doesn't ask questions about anything she hasn't taught you. Study for 5 mins and you'll ACE her exam. If only she taught every course

Great professor, follows the book very closely, and all questions on the midterms and finals are fair.  Lots of memorizing, but you know exactly what is necessary to memorize and what is not.  Exceptional.

This woman is simply astonishing. She is very clear on her expectations and conducts the material as thoroughly and effectively as possible. One of the best professors in uOttawa. She made my semester more bearable. Thank you Professor Carnegie. Good luck to all of you =)
Very clear prof, exams were more than fair.
Good teacher, and a true teacher. Cutiepie, too. She is VERY dry though, which will put you to sleep at least a few times in the semester

Knowledge on the subject is outstanding.  Very fair on midterms and assignments, the content that she covers is all you'll need to know.  Sometimes, a little monotone and boring in her lectures, but the content of her lectures is enough to keep you awake and wanting to learn more.

I love this prof! She's the best! Super clear, very interactive, and knows the material inside and out. She makes it very evident what will be on the exams (and what their weight will be) and stays true to her word. Also, she has a masters in Education, which is rare for a science prof (most are just researchers, Carnegie is a true teacher).

Honestly the best prof The University of Ottawa has. Doesn't mess around. If she teaches it, you have to know it, and nothing else. Makes it very easy and all assignments and midterms are fair.           Love Jackie!

After 3 years in this hell hole of an institution, it still holds true that this professor is by far one of the best here. Amazing lecturer, fair marker, and a delightful personality. Memorize and understand her notes, read through the chapters and don't forget about Mastering- you'll be set & actually walk away having retained useful information.

Carnegie is the best!!! Much better, clearer, and easier (on exams) than Komeroski! Super helpful, EVERYTHING YOU NEED IS IN POWERPOINTS (but still buy textbook to refer to because you'll use the same book for ANP1105, ANP1106, and ANP1107 and it's actually an amazing book). A's are very possible with her, and she answers all questions on V.C.
Prof Carnegie is the nicest lady and very helpful. Super smart and knows how to convey the material so all can understand. the material may be dry at times but not her fault, she IS AWESOME

Had her for ANP1105 and 1106. Great prof, her ppt's are clear. She is very clear about what diagrams & info will be on midterms & exams. Helpful hint to anyone taking ANP. READ THE CHAPTERS IN THE TEXTBOOK over & over till exam (rather than not read & just memorize her ppt notes). ANP1105 I memorized the notes & got B, 1106 read the  book & got A
Not a great prof. Pretty monotonous and she just reads of her slides. I ended up learning almost everything from the textbook. However her powerpoint slides are decent.
Pretty good prof overall. But her teaching is fairly dry though.

Really good prof! She is extremely clear and good at explaining things, and a very nice person in general. She is very thorough, don't be afraid to ask questions in class. Her midterms can be very detailed, so make sure you read the textbook thoroughly and look over the mastering quizzes. Pay attention, she tells you which diagrams will be tested.

Prof Carnegie is really clear on course expectations. Gives hints during class as to what diagrams and material will appear on the exams. Finals and midterms were very fair. Make sure to know diagrams. I suggest to write out notes prior to the lecture and going and listening and adding any other notes she makes during class. Overall good prof!

An overall easy course. I went to 5 lectures all semester and the rest of the time I printed the lecture notes and read over the textbook to make sure I understood everything - you don't need to add extra notes really. Know diagrams - they help and they're on midterms/exams. Practice using sample questions in the online copy of the textbook!

I've had Prof. Carnegie for most of my anatomy classes and for pathophysiology. To me, these classes are extremely hard and annoying but Prof. Carnegie actually made it super easy to understand. She's super organized and such a nice woman. She explains everything in detail and makes sure you understand it.

Great prof. Notes are good. She speaks a little fast, i found it easier to type notes than write them. text book is really useful but i suggest buying ebook as it has online quizzes and animations. overall interesting material. exams are multiple choice and labeling and there's no trick questions. Cool class.
(ANP 1106) Great prof. Made a really boring subject tolerable. No surprises on the exams. Exams were very fair. Overall a wonderful individual and prof.

Absolute pleasure to have this prof. Genuinely wants to help literally 1000+ students succeed, gets back to emails promptly, always available to help, very clear expectations. Incredible prof.ANP courses are A LOT of work, but fascinating material :). She won an award of excellence for teaching as voted by students - very well deserved.

She's all business - burns through course material and keeps the pace up.  She makes midterm and final expectations REALLY clear which is very helpful because there are fewer surprises.  Her guest lecturers were also really interesting guys (for both ANP 1106 and 1107) who were competent at teaching.
Difficult topic, made no easier with her teaching. Knows her stuff, but a very very bad teacher. She sometimes isn't  clear, and can talk way to fast.

Fantastic professor. She knows her material, she cares about her students and wants them to understand. The textbook is really useful since she gets her information from her slides directly from it. If you listen closely, she always mentions important aspects in the material that will be included on the exam. Highly recommend.

Really good prof! It's not the easiest material to learn but she makes it clear what she expects from the students, and her notes and lectures are well organised and easy to understand. She's a nice person too, obviously passionate about what she teaches! Definitely recommend her.

Teaching style is clear and very informative. Always available to answer questions. I've had her for a number of courses now and I can say that she is really there for the students. Take the time to get to know her, she responds well to those students who are actually interested in the material and aren't just looking for a high grade.
Good teacher, Great person. She teaches fairly well, and makes it clear what you need to know. She also shaved her head for cancer!
Prof Carnegie is amazing! She always responds to threads on virtual campus. She is very approachable and makes learning every bone in the body bearable.

lot of work to be done for the course during the semester. the course takes an entire chunk out of your life. lectures were done at over 500km/hr so managed to focus very little in class. fair and straight forward midterms, though.

Jackie Carnegie has been rocking my world for three years now, and she is by far my favorite prof at uOttawa. She also makes for a great honors supervisor and employer! Wonderfully concise and helpful only if you take the time to know her and work with her to achieve the grade you want!!
This prof's teaching is not very good for a first year course. She should retire and Dr. Copeland should take her spot.

Sorry to say, but I found this class quite boring. The slides filled with size 14 font just add to the impending doom upon entering the auditorium. WE LOVE YOU DR.CARNEGIE! YOU ARE THE BEST!!!!  I wanted to cry when she left and Dr. Copeland came...not the Dr. Copeland is bad or anything, he's fine..but Jackie rocks my world. Best Prof at OttawaU, hands down 100%.

She goes through the material like we're medical students....I feel like her only concern is getting through the material, independent of whether we get it or not....most of all she makes you feel stupid in lectures by threatening that some content is "review" when it isn't. I will say that she definitely knows her subject, though!

Very good Prof. Like explained go to class, take notes with her slides and study only that. She had very fair exams. Great class, and yes there is A LOT that she has to go thru but thats the name of the game so come prepared.
Best anatomy prof ive had so far! Midterms/exams are pretty easy since they test exactly whats on her notes. If you can put in the time for this course, it can be a grade booster.
Exams are challenging but fair, pay attention in class and read over the notes.

I'l agree that this woman knows what she's talking about, but just because your a genius, doesnt mean your a good prof.  I find that she has only one concern, getting through the material... not making sure everyone understands it.  Alot of first year students dont have a clue about Anatomy, but goes through the content like we are already experts
Doesn't matter what this woman wears! She is a genius! Works very well with her students and has fair midterms and exams. People who complain about this prof don't make an effort and are just bitter.

She is a genius! She can make even the hardest parts of anatomy seem easy. She can however be rude when she gets upset at the group of students. But then again she does have to deal with a bunch of first years...so who wouldn't be.
Very clear, and loves her subject - definitely the prof to take anatomy with!  Always available to answer questions by email.  Very grandmotherly.

Very good prof, lectures can be annoying and filling her notes during the lectures is also annoying. Exams are easy and the final exam isnt cummalative. Read the textbook and go to the lectures and you ll do great!
She's great
Amazing prof!! Very organized and easy to understand. Alot of material, but if you keep up with her, you'll do fine!
The class is very easy as long as you read the text to fill in the missing questions/blanks in her notes and as long as you MEMORIZE everything. Lectures are, however, extremely boring.
Her class is extremely easy and fair. Midterms adn exams are a breeze if you memorize her notes.
The greatest ANP prof. ever! Her lecture notes are amazing and easy to follow, she is super-helpful, and the midterms and final exam are very fair! This is one class that everyone should take!

she is good. Knows what she is talking about. I think that she expects to much from her students, if they don't put in the effort you aren't going to make them feel guilty for not doing well on the exam...gives so many resources that it is sometimes overwhelming. Some of us are taking 6 other course
Very knowledgeable but her voice is at times monotonous and hard to keep interested in.
if you're a fulltime student... taking a course with her is basically being a fulltime student for her class. forget about the other 3 or 4 that you have.
she goes too fast and covers too much material. it is one thing to have alot of knowledge on a subject, it is another thing to be able to convey that knowledge efficiently.
Jackie is a very good prof. Her class notes are excellent and she is knowledgable. Her teaching style is good as well. I recommend her.

Compared to other profs for this course, she's really easy. She explains everything she tests you on. The more time you put into your course, the better mark you get (and that's the way it should be!).
goes very fast, lots of material, but it's interresting

She has very detailed notes that make it unnecessary to read the text.  Her exams are fair. Repetetive and extreamly boring. Cannot convey what she knows.

Great prof!! Slides really help, as do the course notes. I switched just so that I could be in her ANP 1303 course next semester!
This course is killer.. do not take it unless u have a lot of physiology background and most of all, do not be fooled by the fact that there are no pre-reqs! hidious amts of information.

so much stuff to cover, very dry class
